1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,500
<i> What are we?</i>

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:04,300
<i>It's like we're at
opposite ends of a bridge.</i>

3
00:00:04,300 --> 00:00:06,300
<i> We will cross the bridge...</i>

4
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:08,533
<i>when we're finally ready
to accept each other.</i>

5
00:00:08,533 --> 00:00:10,367
<i>- Are you ready?
- For a while now.</i>

6
00:00:10,367 --> 00:00:12,200
<i> First, for two months...</i>

7
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:13,333
<i> you will eat lunch with me.</i>

8
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:15,433
<i>Aside from lunch,
we'll also have coffee updates.</i>

9
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:16,533
<i> Jealous?</i>

10
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:17,700
<i> Why would I be jealous?</i>

11
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,200
<i> Just a friendly advice.</i>

12
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,600
<i> It's fine if our friend has...</i>

13
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,133
<i> a boyfriend.</i>

14
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,133
<i>Do you know someone
named Sandro Soliman?</i>

15
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,667
<i>I think your dad has
mentioned him before</i>

16
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:30,033
<i>talking about one of
his business ventures</i>

17
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,100
<i> that he was going to enter.</i>

18
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,267
<i>Did this Sandro guy
get in touch with you?</i>

19
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,367
<i> Not really, Uncle.</i>

20
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,800
<i> I don't know him.</i>

21
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,100
<i> I need to know the truth.</i>

22
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:41,100
<i>The Almazans will lead me
to where you are, Papa.</i>

23
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:45,733
You seem to be...

24
00:00:46,133 --> 00:00:48,533
You seem to be enjoying
that a lot.

25
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:52,367
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:54,767
Kiko and I made this together,
so it's just right that...

27
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,500
I enjoy it, right?

28
00:00:57,767 --> 00:00:59,100
Uh.

29
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:01,667
Jade, there...

30
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,533
- There...
- What is it?

31
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,233
["PANGHABANG IKAW" BY
DARREN ESPANTO PLAYING]

32
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:10,200
There is...

33
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:12,267
There's a mosquito!

34
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:13,667
Oh.

35
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,300
There are mosquitoes here.

36
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:17,200
- You might get bitten.
- Oh, right.

37
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:19,667
[CLEARS THROAT]

38
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,400
Sit down.

39
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,500
Don't you want to sit down?

40
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:25,367
Here.

41
00:01:25,367 --> 00:01:27,767
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

42
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:29,333
Start the update.

43
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:33,333
Update?

44
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:36,333
We've been together
the whole time, haven't we?

45
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:39,333
You've seen me all day, so...

46
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:41,100
what update do you still need?

47
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:43,333
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

48
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:44,733
Well, yeah.

49
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,533
But that's my POV.

50
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,367
I would like to see or know...

51
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:51,433
what your point of view is.

52
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,167
What's your story? Your update.

53
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:55,300
Whatever you want.

54
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:56,633
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:01:56,633 --> 00:01:57,767
Well...

56
00:01:58,167 --> 00:02:01,133
Come to think of it,
this day was fun.

57
00:02:01,133 --> 00:02:03,100
I mean, sure.

58
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:06,333
It's chaotic and
exhausting, but...

59
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:08,500
I had fun.

60
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:12,500
I feel like...

61
00:02:12,767 --> 00:02:14,567
I felt more relieved.

62
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,733
Because, in a way,

63
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:20,333
we were able to get justice
for my father's death.

64
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:23,467
And then, Mom would have
peace of mind in Spain.

65
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:26,433
I'm also with my family.

66
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:30,800
My family and that of Kiko's
won't need to fight anymore.

67
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:37,767
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

68
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:43,267
It's always nice
to see you smile, Jade.

69
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:59,800
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:02,800
[CHUCKLING]

71
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,133
What?

72
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,167
Ten minute coffee update
is over.

73
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:08,333
Buh-bye!

74
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:09,700
Good night, Edward.

75
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:21,767
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

76
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:29,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

77
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:51,767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:13,767
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:22,800
[CHESKA CLEARS THROAT]

80
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,367
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

81
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:27,600
Oh.

82
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,333
How great.

83
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:30,833
Is this tent just yours?

84
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,433
You'll fit in there.

85
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:35,800
[CHESKA EXHALES DEEPLY]

87
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,400
My goodness.

88
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,500
Hey, you.

89
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,867
Let's talk.

90
00:04:43,433 --> 00:04:45,833
What's your problem with me?
Why are you so hot-headed?

91
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:47,800
You've been having an attitude
for a while now.

92
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:52,267
Because, you have
no concept of personal...

93
00:04:52,267 --> 00:04:53,367
space.

94
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,633
What?

95
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,700
What word did you just say?

96
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,600
Space?

97
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,933
Can you see my space, huh?

98
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:04,033
Can you see that space?

99
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,000
Cheska, you're just so noisy.

100
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,500
You're so stubborn and dirty.

101
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:12,767
Girl, I just can't stand people
like that, okay?

102
00:05:12,767 --> 00:05:14,067
Even at the hotel,

103
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:15,500
you behave like
it's your own home.

104
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,633
Your brother is
only a part-time owner.

105
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:21,000
[SCOFFS] Well,
what can I do, huh?

106
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,967
That's just how Endayas are.

107
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:27,833
We easily adapt and
feel at home anywhere.

108
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:30,333
Just look at my brother, Kiko.

109
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:31,500
Have you seen him?

110
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,967
He immediately got along
with Gio and your brother Martin

111
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,800
even if they had not seen
each other in a long time.

112
00:05:38,367 --> 00:05:40,967
There, have your space
if that's the issue.

113
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:42,767
We don't need to talk.

114
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:44,433
[CHESKA SCOFFS]

115
00:05:44,433 --> 00:05:45,600
Wait a second.

116
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:48,767
Didn't you even listen
to Art's speech

117
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:50,367
during the team building?

118
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:54,467
Didn't he say that
it's who you do it with?

119
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:58,700
He said that's how
you could do the task.

120
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,833
You didn't even bother
to apply it yourself.

121
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:04,667
[MOODY MUSIC PLAYING]

122
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:05,633
[TRIXIE SCOFFS]

123
00:06:06,067 --> 00:06:07,633
You're giving me a headache.

124
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:15,433
[FAN BLOWS]

125
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:20,433
[SCOFFS]

126
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:27,400
[MOODY MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:31,967
Here.

128
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,567
I know you're not used
to the heat.

129
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,033
I can't sleep because of you.

130
00:06:36,033 --> 00:06:39,567
You keep going like this.
You'll be like that all night.

131
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,400
Use it!

132
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:45,033
Thank you!

133
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,167
[CHESKA] You're welcome!

134
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:53,133
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:06:53,867 --> 00:07:00,800
[CHESKA SNORING]

136
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:05,567
What kind of person can go
to sleep right away?

137
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,833
She really feels at home.

138
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:12,000
[SNORING CONTINUES]

139
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:16,833
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:22,467
[WAVES CRASHING]

141
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:24,067
- Come with me.
- Oh.

142
00:07:25,467 --> 00:07:26,467
Gio, what is it?

143
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:27,633
We'll have a talk, Luna.

144
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:29,000
I don't want to!

145
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,167
You don't want to?

146
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,767
You don't want to?

147
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,167
Gio, put me down!

148
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,167
I don't care if people hear us!

149
00:07:35,167 --> 00:07:39,833
[BRIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:42,000
Fine! I'll come with you.
Just let me down.

151
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,833
[GIO] I'll bring you down and
you will come with me.

152
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:45,433
If you run away,

153
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:46,833
I'm going to carry you
like a sack of rice.

154
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:47,967
Do you understand?

155
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:51,667
Okay, just put me down.

156
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:55,867
Hop on.

157
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,533
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:58,900
Get in!

159
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,433
[SCOFFS]

160
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:19,500
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

161
00:08:38,867 --> 00:08:45,833
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO VASQUEZ
PLAYING]

162
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:07,833
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

163
00:09:22,867 --> 00:09:29,833
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

164
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,967
Hey, wait!
Where is he going?

165
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:42,533
[GIO] He's going
to leave us here.

166
00:09:43,867 --> 00:09:46,000
We're just going to talk, right?

167
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,567
He will come back
when I call him.

168
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:51,700
He won't come back until
you talk properly with me.

169
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:52,867
Gio!

170
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:54,700
What, are you going
to start now?

171
00:09:54,700 --> 00:10:01,667
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

172
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:07,267
What? Just tell me, I'll listen!

173
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:09,433
Just say it, Luna!

174
00:10:09,433 --> 00:10:11,233
You are childish.

175
00:10:12,767 --> 00:10:14,133
Really, Gio?

176
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,233
Did you have to come
to this point?

177
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:19,100
I tried talking to you properly,
but you wouldn't.

178
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,800
It is your fault
that we got to this point.

179
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,000
Alright.

180
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,433
What if the boatman leaves?

181
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:25,833
What if he doesn't come back?

182
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,933
Do you even think, Gio?

183
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:31,100
You talk a lot,
but keep avoiding my question.

184
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:33,400
- What happened to you, Luna?
- Nothing!

185
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,767
Nothing happened!

186
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:43,200
Something happened because
the Luna I knew in Manila

187
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,467
is different from the Luna
I met on this island!

188
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,267
People change, Gio.

189
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,133
I know, but there's a reason.

190
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,300
And that's what I want to know.

191
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:00,933
You wouldn't change
if nothing happened to you.

192
00:11:01,233 --> 00:11:02,767
Now, tell me, Luna.

193
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,833
What happened to you?

194
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:09,467
[SOFT, DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

195
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,233
You don't believe that Roi
killed your fathers anymore?

196
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,100
I just wanted to be sure.

197
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:24,433
It's possible that other people
held a grudge against them.

198
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:29,867
At the moment, Roi is the
only one who has a motive

199
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:32,267
and said he was at the
crime scene at the time.

200
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:35,267
Didn't Dad
or Uncle Michael report

201
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:37,267
about anything before they died?

202
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:40,433
Maybe someone tried to kill them
or someone's mad at them?

203
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,400
Nothing.

204
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:45,000
If they did, we'd have it
included in the investigation.

205
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:48,633
Maybe...

206
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:53,200
It's best to talk to your lawyer
about your speculations.

207
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,933
It's possible that Roi
is getting through your head.

208
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:03,000
Do you need anything else, Leon?

209
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:05,267
No, sir.

210
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:07,433
And, Leon...

211
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,967
Wherever your fathers are
right now,

212
00:12:11,567 --> 00:12:13,500
I'm sure they're at peace.

213
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:16,567
I hope you find that, too.

214
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:20,533
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYS]

215
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,533
I just have to do something.

216
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:37,233
Can't I just want to change?

217
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:39,067
Can't I not be Solenn anymore?

218
00:12:39,067 --> 00:12:40,533
You think I'd believe that?

219
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:43,333
I know you love what you did
back in Manila.

220
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,000
You don't really want
to be here!

221
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,900
That's not me!

222
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:56,500
You may fool others with that,
but I know who you really are.

223
00:12:58,633 --> 00:13:00,467
Just call a boatman, will you?

224
00:13:00,467 --> 00:13:02,133
This is going nowhere.

225
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:05,000
- We're not done yet!
- Why?

226
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:07,600
Because you haven't heard
what you wanted to hear?

227
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,233
That I'm just pretending
right now?

228
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:11,333
Yes!

229
00:13:12,367 --> 00:13:14,033
Because if you were
pretending then,

230
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:16,267
you also admit that
what we had wasn't real!

231
00:13:16,567 --> 00:13:18,900
Everything we went through...

232
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:23,267
You can't just convince yourself

233
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:26,500
to wake up one day and decide
that it never happened.

234
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,067
I never said it didn't happen.

235
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:35,100
But that's what
you're showing me now.

236
00:13:36,533 --> 00:13:39,533
That's what you make me feel.

237
00:13:42,633 --> 00:13:46,167
You avoid me, you won't talk
to me unless about work.

238
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:48,900
Your siblings don't even know
we met back in Manila!

239
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:52,067
So, I don't understand
why you're acting like that.

240
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:57,600
You just discarded me.

241
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:06,633
We were happy, weren't we?

242
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:16,000
Was that just nothing to you?

243
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:24,667
[SIGHS]

244
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,567
I've let go of everything that
happened to me in the past.

245
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:32,100
I'm here now.

246
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:34,500
This is the Luna I know.

247
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,433
If you can't accept that,
there's nothing I can do.

248
00:14:43,567 --> 00:14:46,533
[SOFT, DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

249
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:09,667
Hey, Leon.

250
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:13,533
I thought you're going home.

251
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:16,433
I'm just waiting for my driver
to get the car.

252
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:22,400
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

253
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:34,167
- [ENGINE REVVS]
- [THUDS]

254
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:35,367
[TIRES SCREECH]

255
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,367
Sandro Soliman?

256
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:50,367
Do you know him?

257
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:53,133
Uh... No.

258
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:55,767
I just read what was written.

259
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,600
Is he a local?

260
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,600
No, just visiting.

261
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:04,300
His son just
reported him missing.

262
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:07,700
Alright. Take care.

263
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:12,233
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:16:25,667 --> 00:16:27,100
[CELLPHONE CAMERA CLICKS]

265
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,033
[KIKO] Jade!

266
00:16:28,433 --> 00:16:31,100
[CELLPHONE CAMERA CLICKS]

267
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,467
- Jade.
- Wait!

268
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:33,633
- Let's go.
- Wait, wait.

269
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:34,433
I'm just taking pictures.

270
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:36,567
Maybe I can get
some inspiration

271
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,533
for the kids' painting sessions.

272
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:40,000
[CELLPHONE CAMERA CLICKS]

273
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,600
Did you sleep early last night?

274
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:45,667
Yeah. Mm, Edward and I
didn't stay up long either.

275
00:16:45,667 --> 00:16:47,400
He just wanted me
to tell him stories.

276
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,567
We're going home again.

277
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:54,333
Back to the real world.
[CHUCKLES]

278
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:55,533
Yeah, right.

279
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:58,367
Too bad Leon didn't get
to experience this.

280
00:16:58,367 --> 00:17:01,100
If he were here,
it would've been so much fun.

281
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,267
- For sure.
- [SNAKE HISSING]

282
00:17:04,267 --> 00:17:05,300
[KIKO GROANS]

283
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:06,867
- Ouch! Jade! It hurts!
- Kiko! Kiko! Kiko!

284
00:17:06,867 --> 00:17:08,300
What happened?! Oh my god!

285
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,667
- I got bitten by a snake!
- You got bitten?! Oh my god!

286
00:17:09,667 --> 00:17:11,233
- Oh my god!
- [GROANS]

287
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:12,367
You got bitten! Kiko!

288
00:17:12,367 --> 00:17:13,633
- Ouch!
- Oh no! What do I do?

289
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:14,700
- Jade...
- What should I do?!

290
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,300
- Jade, it hurts!
- Kiko-- Help!

291
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,600
Help! Wait!

292
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:18,900
Wait, wait. Just breathe.
Hold on.

293
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:20,467
Calm down, wait! Wait!

294
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:22,233
- Wait, I saw in movies...
- Ouch! Ouch!

295
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:23,600
...that when you get bitten
by a snake,

296
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,867
you have to suck
the venom out.

297
00:17:24,867 --> 00:17:26,467
- You're going to suck it out?!
- What?!

298
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:28,300
I'm not sucking it!
What do you mean suck it?!

299
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:29,633
- No! I'm not sucking that!
- Jade!

300
00:17:29,633 --> 00:17:30,567
What if the poison
transfers to me?!

301
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:31,800
Jade, oh my god!
I think I'm going to die!

302
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,667
- No, you're not-- Okay fine!
- Ouch! Ouch!

303
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:35,433
I'll do it!

304
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:38,500
I'll do it! Here! Here!
Okay. [BREATHES HEAVILY]

305
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,600
- What?
- Where?

306
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,400
- [KIKO GROANS]
- Hurry! Come on!

307
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,633
- Sit! Sit! Here!
- Ouch! Ouch!

308
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:43,600
I'll suck it out! Hurry!
Come on!

309
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,767
- Lift it! Hurry.
- Here-- Ouch!

310
00:17:45,467 --> 00:17:46,733
- What happened?
- Art!

311
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,433
He got bitten by a snake!

312
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:49,500
- Snake?!
- [KIKO GRUNTS]

313
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,867
Wait, what color was the snake?

314
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:52,867
What? It was like...

315
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:55,800
Kind of black with brown spots.
Something like that.

316
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:56,933
- Maybe a wolf snake.
- Huh?!

317
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:59,733
- [ART] But it's not venomous.
- [KIKO] Ouch! Ouch!

318
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,200
[GROANING CONTINUES]

319
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,500
- [JADE] Kiko?
- Mm?

320
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,933
Do you have a mark on your butt?

321
00:18:04,933 --> 00:18:06,333
- Huh?
- Huh?

322
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:08,767
Because my grandpa said
if you have a mark on your butt,

323
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:09,833
it means bad luck.

324
00:18:09,833 --> 00:18:12,200
I don't have a mark on my butt.
Maybe you do!

325
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,700
I only get into accidents
whenever I'm with you.

326
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:15,900
The time I choked,

327
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:18,267
when you almost got hit
by a motorcycle, and then this--

328
00:18:18,267 --> 00:18:19,800
[GROANS] Ouch! Ouch!

329
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,267
That's three times?!
Oh, Ms. Jade,

330
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,567
that's a different kind
of bad luck.

331
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,567
Huh? What bad luck?

332
00:18:24,567 --> 00:18:26,767
Sari, what is that now?

333
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:29,267
Sir, that's a belief
of the elders

334
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:30,767
here in the province.

335
00:18:30,767 --> 00:18:32,967
When two people are always
unlucky together,

336
00:18:32,967 --> 00:18:34,567
it means they're cursed.

337
00:18:34,567 --> 00:18:37,700
Well, there are certain beliefs
in the provinces.

338
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:38,933
Oh dear, Ms. Jade.

339
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:41,367
If I were you,
I'd have that removed.

340
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:43,400
I know how to remove it.

341
00:18:43,867 --> 00:18:44,967
Do you want to?

342
00:18:44,967 --> 00:18:52,200
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,867
[WAVES CRASHING]

344
00:18:59,233 --> 00:19:05,967
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:19:20,867 --> 00:19:27,833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

346
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:36,867
[WAVES CRASHING]

347
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:42,867
[WAVES CRASHING]

348
00:19:45,567 --> 00:19:49,633
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:50,733
[GIO] The bridge...

350
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:58,000
You said before that we were
on opposite ends of the bridge.

351
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,767
I couldn't cross
the bridge, Gio.

352
00:20:08,867 --> 00:20:10,000
So let's stop.

353
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:17,500
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

354
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:24,833
[BOAT ROARING]

355
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:37,967
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:42,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

357
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:47,000
[LEON]
<i> Someone's looking for him.</i>

358
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:50,500
<i> Could it be his family?</i>

359
00:21:00,633 --> 00:21:03,100
<i> Why are you looking
for my father?</i>

360
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:11,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

361
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,800
[JUSTIN]<i> Why are you looking
</i> at my brother like that?

362
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:28,567
Sorry, sorry! I didn't see you.
<i> Are you okay?</i>

363
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:30,133
<i> - Yeah.
- I didn't mean to.</i>

364
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:41,567
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

365
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,167
What is it?

366
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:03,667
Good morning, sir.
How may I help you?

367
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:06,233
I just wanted to ask a question
at your front desk.

368
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:09,167
We don't have anyone in
right now.

369
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:11,600
You can ask me instead.

370
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,200
I work here, too.

371
00:22:16,367 --> 00:22:19,333
I was wondering if I could post
some missing posters here.

372
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:21,267
Oh, I'm sorry, sir.

373
00:22:21,267 --> 00:22:24,767
We only post hotel activities
on the bulletin board.

374
00:22:24,767 --> 00:22:26,833
But I can tell our staff
about it.

375
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:29,733
If we ever see, uh...

376
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:33,767
Mr. Sandro?

377
00:22:33,767 --> 00:22:35,200
Sandro Soliman.

378
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:36,867
My father.

379
00:22:37,467 --> 00:22:38,600
Oh, okay.

380
00:22:39,267 --> 00:22:40,867
I'll tell our staff
to keep an eye out.

381
00:22:41,633 --> 00:22:42,700
Thank you.

382
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:47,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

383
00:22:57,867 --> 00:23:00,233
Folder? Uncle Mike has a folder?

384
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:02,433
<i>- I'll stay here.
- What are you gonna do?</i>

385
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:03,433
<i> Just keep an eye out.</i>

386
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:04,800
<i> Why did you shut down
the first time?</i>

387
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,900
<i> There was a fire.</i>

388
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:08,167
<i> There aren't any traces
of a fire anywhere.</i>

389
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:10,900
<i> Whatever your decision is,
I support it.</i>

390
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:12,167
<i> If you still love her,</i>

391
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:14,633
<i>find out the answers
to all your questions.</i>

392
00:23:14,633 --> 00:23:16,333
<i> And use it to fight for her.</i>

393
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:18,500
<i>Whatever you have going on,
I'm all for it.</i>

394
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:20,800
<i>But, she's good
for the business.</i>

395
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:22,567
<i>Most importantly,
she's good for your heart.</i>

396
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:23,800
<i> Are you...</i>

397
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:26,733
<i>Are you the ones
who want to break a curse?</i>

398
00:23:26,733 --> 00:23:28,333
<i> - Wait, no!
- No!</i>

